pr_body:
Fixes #5 

I have created the API_Doc with 2 classes for now and added operations for the Loan class only.

The database is set up successfully.
![Screenshot from 2021-06-08 19-58-22](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49719371/121203793-046e8900-c894-11eb-9052-95769ba4b3b3.png)

![creditrisk_poc](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49719371/121204126-4a2b5180-c894-11eb-9eb2-60d1dbe04731.gif)

We are facing a problem that all the classes should be displayed at `http://localhost:8080/creditrisk_api/`
but we are only getting the EntryPoint.

We (@farazkhanfk7) discussed the problem, which might be due to URIs of properties & class which is not dereferenceable by hydrus.
as I have used 
`"NPL": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Purvanshsingh/creditrisk-poc/main/NonPerformingLoan.json"` in API_Doc context.

[{'comment_id': 650022885, 'comment_body': 'What you are doing here is not the proper way.
What you want to do is:
1. build the ApiDoc programmatically (ok done)
2. save the JSON-LD string in a file (`json.dumps(doc)` -> `ApiDoc.jsonld`)
3. if you want to have the file in a Python dictionary: create a new file `apidoc.py` that does: 
```
doc = None
with open("ApiDoc.jsonld") as d:
    doc = json.loads(d.read())
```
All this has to be put under `if __name__ == "__main__":`, it tells the Python interpreter to run all the code when the command `$ python creditrisk_poc_docwriter.py` is run; as it is now only the last lines will be run but `doc` will be undefined.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 6, 11, 14, 27, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Mec-iS', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 650028622, 'comment_body': 'Okay, will fix this.

pr_title: ApiDoc Automation script created & mock portfolio data generator refectored.
pr_body:
Fixes #15 

As of now, we create all the classes and properties in ApiDoc using docwriter.py manually.
I have created the script which will parse the `NonPerformingLoan.jsonld` and can create hydra classes & properties for ApiDoc.

**NonPerformingLoan.jsonld --> ApiDoc**

Methods used to parse the jsonld-ld are defined in `NPLVocab_parser.py` 
It can be used as:
```python
import NPLVocab_parse as parser

npl_vocab = parser.get_npl_vocab()
classes = parser.get_all_classes(npl_vocab)
hydra_classes = parser.create_hydra_classes(classes)
```
The ApiDoc generated by the new script is tested with the postman. and all the tests are passing as well. 

> We just need to run `docwriter.py` to create new ApiDoc everytime it will generate classes & properties from JSON-LD.

![Screenshot from 2021-06-29 18-44-45](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49719371/123823828-28653d80-d91b-11eb-929f-a869313adba6.png)

`mock_porfolio_generator.py` is also refactored.
creating objects in sequence.

**CounterParty --> Loan --> Collateral**
